<TITLE> JU students barricade Dhaka-Aricha highway </TITLE>
<TEXT>
 Dhaka, Aug 22 (bdnews24.com)  Students of Jahangirnagar University demanding resignation of chief adviser Fakhruddin Ahmed have barricaded the Dhaka-Aricha highway since Wednesday morning. The agitating students also burned an effigy of law adviser Mainul Hosein while demanding the lifting of the state of emergency. Earlier at 10:00am, students from different dormitories took out processions and approached the Dairy Farm gate, but police stopped them. A clash ensued leaving proctor Syed Kamrul Ahsan and 20 students and journalists injured. Police clubbed the agitating students. Additional superintendent of police Nazrul and some others were injured when the students threw stones. At one stage of the clash, police retreated and positioned themselves outside the university gate. Students then blocked the highway. Jahangirnagar University chapter of pro-Awami League Bangladesh Chhatra League, pro-BNP Jatiyatabadi Chhatra Dal and pro-Communist Party of Bangladesh Bangladesh Chhatra Union leaders were present. The demonstrators piled up tires on the highway and set them ablaze. Three students, Masum Billah, Mahbub Alam Munna and Rasheduzzaman were severely injured in the clashes. Proctor Syed Kamrul Ahsan received first aid. Long-distance commuters were facing severe problems due to the barricade, and a long queue of passenger buses and trucks remained stranded in Savar and Nabinagar. bdnews24.com
